1
00:00:20,337 --> 00:00:23,080
What madness is this? To take our son away as a hostage!

2
00:00:23,523 --> 00:00:25,600
This is a royal mandate from King Bayinnaung.

3
00:00:25,624 --> 00:00:29,280
To defy him is to be branded a rebel.

4
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:33,520
Nares, I loved you like my own brother.

5
00:00:34,040 --> 00:00:37,080
I, too, see you as my own elder brother.

6
00:00:41,240 --> 00:00:43,880
My mother and my siblings were lured to Ayutthaya

7
00:00:43,950 --> 00:00:45,120
and are now being held as captives.

8
00:00:45,480 --> 00:00:47,360
My father went to negotiate with King Mahinthrathirat,

9
00:00:47,481 --> 00:00:50,000
But he has not yet returned, and his whereabouts remain unknown.

10
00:00:50,030 --> 00:00:52,760
This is a grave insolence.

11
00:00:53,160 --> 00:00:55,680
For we shall march our armies to Ayutthaya.

12
00:01:00,137 --> 00:01:04,760
In the past, I believed that war was simply about killing strangers

13
00:01:04,957 --> 00:01:06,640
or those not of our kind.

14
00:01:07,650 --> 00:01:11,560
We both were meant to stay on the same side forever.

15
00:01:12,880 --> 00:01:13,881
Was that not the promise?

16
00:01:14,390 --> 00:01:16,120
If you stand by my side,

17
00:01:17,570 --> 00:01:19,077
I shall stand by yours.

18
00:01:20,120 --> 00:01:23,121
[Sanphet Prasat Throne Hall, Ayutthaya]

19
00:01:25,480 --> 00:01:29,000
[Friday, the 6th Waxing Moon of the 12th Lunar Month]

20
00:01:29,183 --> 00:01:30,184
In the Year of the Snake,

21
00:01:31,000 --> 00:01:33,120
following the conquest of Ayutthaya,

22
00:01:33,600 --> 00:01:36,000
King Bayinnaung of Hongsawadi

23
00:01:36,440 --> 00:01:38,840
crowned my father

24
00:01:39,520 --> 00:01:42,517
as King Maha Thammarachathirat,

25
00:01:43,240 --> 00:01:45,950
to reign over the Kingdom of Ayutthaya.

26
00:01:58,357 --> 00:01:59,737
Proclaiming His Majesty’s name

27
00:02:00,237 --> 00:02:04,160
Somdet Phra Chao Sanphet Wongkura Suriyodom,

28
00:02:04,590 --> 00:02:07,720
Borom Maha Thammarachathirat Rames,

29
00:02:08,250 --> 00:02:11,360
Pawaret Dhammikarat Dechochai,

30
00:02:12,320 --> 00:02:14,680
Phrommathep Adithep Narubodintra,

31
00:02:15,320 --> 00:02:19,880
Phuminthara Thep Sommutirat Borommapophit.

32
00:02:20,760 --> 00:02:22,600
Long Live the King!

33
00:02:24,017 --> 00:02:27,400
King Mahinthrathirat was escorted,

34
00:02:28,400 --> 00:02:29,840
along with his ministers and officials,

35
00:02:30,177 --> 00:02:33,560
and all the ladies of the inner court to Hongsawadi.

36
00:03:04,960 --> 00:03:07,880
From that day forth,

37
00:03:08,700 --> 00:03:10,520
my life would never be the same.

38
00:04:30,590 --> 00:04:31,800
I do not understand.

39
00:04:33,080 --> 00:04:35,280
In Inwa and Prome,

40
00:04:35,640 --> 00:04:37,520
you sent our own to rule.

41
00:04:37,943 --> 00:04:40,680
Why then, is Ayutthaya not governed by our own?

42
00:04:43,400 --> 00:04:46,240
How can one race rule another?

43
00:04:47,080 --> 00:04:49,001
It would only sow the seeds of rebellion.

44
00:04:52,240 --> 00:04:54,560
King Maha Thammaracha is the fitting choice.

45
00:04:55,880 --> 00:04:57,720
Having dwelt in Ayutthaya

46
00:04:58,840 --> 00:05:00,720
since the reign of King Chairacha,

47
00:05:01,417 --> 00:05:05,760
he knows the inner workings of the court and its people.

48
00:05:06,697 --> 00:05:08,720
Ayutthaya is a supreme city,

49
00:05:09,480 --> 00:05:10,721
rich in grain,

50
00:05:10,857 --> 00:05:13,480
thriving in trade, and gifted with a strategic site.

51
00:05:14,160 --> 00:05:17,800
You have granted King Maha Thammaracha total rule,

52
00:05:18,960 --> 00:05:20,280
I fear for the future.

53
00:05:22,480 --> 00:05:26,200
For throughout history, those who sit upon that throne

54
00:05:26,720 --> 00:05:29,080
have never bowed their heads to any man.

55
00:05:37,357 --> 00:05:40,440
One hundred chang of silver and thirteen of gold,

56
00:05:41,560 --> 00:05:43,000
I bestow upon you.

57
00:05:44,010 --> 00:05:46,880
Use them to restore the temples and the land,

58
00:05:47,400 --> 00:05:50,000
scarred by the flames of war,

59
00:05:50,960 --> 00:05:52,520
until they flourish as they did before.

60
00:05:55,961 --> 00:05:57,800
Your Mercy is boundless, Your Majesty.

61
00:06:00,123 --> 00:06:01,620
What I have given,

62
00:06:02,720 --> 00:06:04,760
is nothing compared to what I shall ask.

63
00:06:07,440 --> 00:06:09,600
What is it that You desire, Your Majesty?

64
00:06:17,200 --> 00:06:19,001
Hongsawadi’s gold

65
00:06:20,322 --> 00:06:22,400
in exchange for the gold of Ayutthaya.

66
00:06:27,370 --> 00:06:31,480
We ask for Princess Suphankalaya, your daughter,

67
00:06:32,310 --> 00:06:34,481
to be my royal consort.

68
00:06:47,720 --> 00:06:49,000
And if we were to resist,

69
00:06:49,400 --> 00:06:51,120
and refuse to offer Sister?

70
00:06:54,270 --> 00:06:57,710
Offering a royal princess as a consort

71
00:06:58,337 --> 00:07:00,360
to foster ties between our two realms

72
00:07:01,840 --> 00:07:03,960
is a custom long observed throughout the ages.

73
00:07:04,350 --> 00:07:07,160
But not to an elder, old enough to be her own father!

74
00:07:08,840 --> 00:07:12,200
Regardless of who he may be, I find no joy in this, Father.

75
00:07:13,440 --> 00:07:14,441
My child,

76
00:07:15,557 --> 00:07:17,560
no soul finds joy in this.

77
00:07:18,920 --> 00:07:21,720
But King Bayinnaung's request for your hand

78
00:07:22,797 --> 00:07:24,400
is an ultimate gesture of alliance.

79
00:07:26,280 --> 00:07:27,320
Should you accept,

80
00:07:29,017 --> 00:07:30,720
Ayutthaya and Hongsawadi

81
00:07:31,290 --> 00:07:33,560
shall be united as one Golden Land forevermore.

82
00:07:35,130 --> 00:07:36,480
But to refuse

83
00:07:38,277 --> 00:07:39,840
is to insult His Royal Honor.

84
00:07:44,120 --> 00:07:45,200
That means…

85
00:07:47,360 --> 00:07:48,400
War.

86
00:07:53,320 --> 00:07:54,921
I will go and plead with King Bayinnaung,

87
00:07:55,600 --> 00:07:56,840
to spare my sister from this fate.

88
00:07:57,403 --> 00:07:59,080
He will surely listen to me, Father.

89
00:07:59,560 --> 00:08:00,561
Dam.

90
00:08:01,597 --> 00:08:02,598
Dam.

91
00:08:17,138 --> 00:08:19,560
I have come to seek an audience with the King of Hongsawadi,

92
00:08:19,897 --> 00:08:21,520
for I have a matter of great urgency to present.

93
00:08:26,490 --> 00:08:27,800
What is it you intend to plead?

94
00:08:27,891 --> 00:08:30,200
The matter of Princess Suphankalaya is none of your concern!

95
00:08:31,503 --> 00:08:34,520
How can it not be? Nares is my brother.

96
00:08:34,897 --> 00:08:36,440
His sorrow is my own.

97
00:08:37,810 --> 00:08:40,811
Besides, Grandfather seeks a true alliance with Ayutthaya.

98
00:08:41,240 --> 00:08:44,200
If he knew their hearts were unwilling, he would not force this blow.

99
00:08:44,640 --> 00:08:47,360
Your Grandfather knows full well they are unwilling.

100
00:09:01,037 --> 00:09:03,160
His demand for Princess Suphankalaya

101
00:09:04,360 --> 00:09:07,240
is merely to gauge King Maha Thammaracha’s heart,

102
00:09:07,437 --> 00:09:09,320
to see if his loyalty remains true.

103
00:09:11,770 --> 00:09:13,480
But we have only just fought side by side,

104
00:09:14,071 --> 00:09:15,600
facing life and death together on the battlefield.

105
00:09:18,600 --> 00:09:19,920
Today, yes.

106
00:09:21,080 --> 00:09:22,880
Ayutthaya remains a friend.

107
00:09:23,577 --> 00:09:25,840
But tomorrow, should they grow strong again,

108
00:09:26,030 --> 00:09:27,440
that friendship may quickly turn to enemy.

109
00:09:28,640 --> 00:09:29,640
For this reason,

110
00:09:30,240 --> 00:09:33,880
your Grandfather demands the Princess,

111
00:09:34,241 --> 00:09:35,960
to dwell within the walls of Hongsawadi,

112
00:09:36,560 --> 00:09:38,561
serving as nothing more than a royal hostage.

113
00:09:41,583 --> 00:09:42,584
Hostage?

114
00:09:43,483 --> 00:09:46,360
Do not forget... at this very hour,

115
00:09:47,040 --> 00:09:49,280
The people of Ayutthaya and Phitsanulok,

116
00:09:50,041 --> 00:09:51,720
from high-born princes to the lowest commoners,

117
00:09:52,190 --> 00:09:54,560
are but captives of Hongsawadi.

118
00:09:55,691 --> 00:09:58,680
Why then, do you trouble yourself with the feelings of mere slaves?

119
00:09:58,750 --> 00:09:59,751
Mingyi Swa.

120
00:11:08,503 --> 00:11:09,504
Go that way!

121
00:11:10,390 --> 00:11:11,391
Hey!

122
00:11:13,760 --> 00:11:15,800
You!

123
00:11:16,480 --> 00:11:17,481
Pitch the tents.

124
00:11:18,800 --> 00:11:20,720
The rest of you, go fetch water from the stream.

125
00:11:21,350 --> 00:11:22,351
Follow me.

126
00:11:24,597 --> 00:11:25,598
Quick.

127
00:11:34,343 --> 00:11:35,344
Go!

128
00:11:54,857 --> 00:11:56,723
Your Royal Brother has arrived to see you, Your Highness.

129
00:12:01,577 --> 00:12:02,578
You may leave.

130
00:12:09,510 --> 00:12:12,160
Sister, please bear this burden a little longer.

131
00:12:13,143 --> 00:12:15,200
In just a few more days, we shall reach Hongsawadi.

132
00:12:22,110 --> 00:12:23,360
And there,

133
00:12:26,240 --> 00:12:29,320
at the Inner Court, who else resides within those walls?

134
00:12:34,243 --> 00:12:37,480
King Bayinnaung once had three Great Queens.

135
00:12:38,000 --> 00:12:41,360
But Chief Queen Consort Atula Thiri Maha Yaza Dewi

136
00:12:41,800 --> 00:12:44,880
and Queen Yaza Dewi have both passed away.

137
00:12:45,560 --> 00:12:47,477
Only Queen Sanda Dewi

138
00:12:48,561 --> 00:12:49,870
remains as a Senior Consort,

139
00:12:51,143 --> 00:12:52,324
along with Junior Queens

140
00:12:53,480 --> 00:12:55,520
and dozens of concubines.

141
00:12:56,481 --> 00:12:59,000
They are all daughters and granddaughters of vassal kings.

142
00:13:03,560 --> 00:13:05,440
And who among them wields the ultimate power?

143
00:13:07,177 --> 00:13:08,240
There is no one.

144
00:13:08,890 --> 00:13:12,440
King Bayinnaung honored his Chief Queen above all,

145
00:13:13,237 --> 00:13:15,640
for she was the sister of King Tabinshwehti.

146
00:13:16,280 --> 00:13:17,760
While she lived,

147
00:13:18,270 --> 00:13:21,320
she sat beneath the White Umbrella as an equal to the King himself.

148
00:13:22,200 --> 00:13:23,720
Since her passing,

149
00:13:24,103 --> 00:13:26,104
he has raised no other to her rank.

150
00:13:29,000 --> 00:13:30,240
Then that is well.

151
00:13:32,401 --> 00:13:35,800
Why do you ask? What are you planning?

152
00:13:38,520 --> 00:13:39,921
I do not know yet.

153
00:13:41,230 --> 00:13:44,720
I will observe, and wait.

154
00:13:46,840 --> 00:13:49,640
But I refuse to remain a hostage until the day I die.

155
00:14:13,663 --> 00:14:14,680
Hurry up!

156
00:14:21,617 --> 00:14:22,618
Ouch!

157
00:14:23,010 --> 00:14:25,240
What are you doing? Get up!

158
00:14:26,590 --> 00:14:28,800
Agh! I think... I think my leg is broken!

159
00:14:30,770 --> 00:14:32,360
Here, Sir.

160
00:14:37,370 --> 00:14:38,371
Here.

161
00:15:01,297 --> 00:15:02,400
What are you doing?

162
00:15:03,870 --> 00:15:04,960
Run! Go now!

163
00:15:36,840 --> 00:15:38,237
Captives are escaping!

164
00:15:39,303 --> 00:15:40,920
Help! The captives are fleeing!

165
00:15:43,120 --> 00:15:44,960
My Lord... the captives... they have escaped!

166
00:15:45,320 --> 00:15:46,321
They went that way.

167
00:15:48,090 --> 00:15:49,091
Follow them.

168
00:15:50,840 --> 00:15:51,841
Captives are escaping!

169
00:15:52,720 --> 00:15:54,520
Follow me! This way!

170
00:15:56,803 --> 00:15:57,804
What has happened?

171
00:15:58,080 --> 00:16:01,040
Captives have fled, Your Highness. The Burmese are giving chase.

172
00:16:10,710 --> 00:16:11,711
Brother.

173
00:16:13,000 --> 00:16:14,601
Nares, this way.

174
00:16:22,963 --> 00:16:23,964
Stop!

175
00:16:28,897 --> 00:16:31,600
Prince Nares, have mercy on us, Your Highness.

176
00:16:41,560 --> 00:16:42,640
What have you done?

177
00:16:44,757 --> 00:16:47,170
They tried to escape. We were merely securing them, Your Highness.

178
00:16:48,000 --> 00:16:49,240
Securing them? You are slaughtering my people!

179
00:16:51,103 --> 00:16:53,804
- But these captives...
- These men are master craftsmen.

180
00:16:55,050 --> 00:16:58,280
There is a Royal Decree for them to serve in Hongsawadi.

181
00:17:00,390 --> 00:17:02,800
By wounding and killing them like this,

182
00:17:03,783 --> 00:17:05,601
do you not fear the consequences?

183
00:17:05,680 --> 00:17:08,560
The captives resisted and refused to be taken quietly.

184
00:17:08,730 --> 00:17:11,320
Thus, we were forced to strike, as dictated by the Code of War.

185
00:17:11,690 --> 00:17:14,521
To slay a fleeing prisoner is no crime, Your Highess.

186
00:17:25,870 --> 00:17:26,871
Prince Nares!

187
00:18:07,400 --> 00:18:09,160
Look, the captives.

188
00:18:09,343 --> 00:18:10,440
I am no captive.

189
00:18:10,500 --> 00:18:13,000
I said you're a captive, so you are one!

190
00:18:13,080 --> 00:18:14,760
Teach him a lesson for me.

191
00:18:15,463 --> 00:18:16,880
- Ouch!
- Again!

192
00:18:42,840 --> 00:18:45,960
If someone must be blamed, then blame me.

193
00:18:56,183 --> 00:18:57,184
The fault is mine alone.

194
00:18:57,960 --> 00:18:59,120
I failed to restrain them in time.

195
00:19:00,903 --> 00:19:01,904
You are not at fault, Brother.

196
00:19:03,557 --> 00:19:04,720
No one is at fault here.

197
00:19:05,830 --> 00:19:08,880
By the law, escaping captives may be slain.

198
00:19:13,160 --> 00:19:17,000
If you know the law, then why do you still burn with rage?

199
00:19:19,930 --> 00:19:20,931
I am enraged.

200
00:19:22,040 --> 00:19:24,800
Enraged that the people of Ayutthaya must live as captives of Hongsawadi.

201
00:19:27,200 --> 00:19:28,320
But upon reflection,

202
00:19:29,320 --> 00:19:31,080
there is no difference between those men and me.

203
00:19:33,480 --> 00:19:34,481
Nonsense.

204
00:19:36,157 --> 00:19:37,640
I heard what your father said.

205
00:19:39,310 --> 00:19:42,120
Both my sister and I, we are nothing more than hostages.

206
00:19:46,610 --> 00:19:47,811
Do not listen to those words.

207
00:19:49,000 --> 00:19:51,001
Grandfather favors you greatly. You know this to be true.

208
00:19:51,080 --> 00:19:53,160
- He only favors my skill in battle.
- To be favored is to be favored.

209
00:19:53,760 --> 00:19:55,161
Whatever the reason for his favor, it matters not.

210
00:19:59,600 --> 00:20:00,440
Let it be this way.

211
00:20:01,760 --> 00:20:03,280
Once we return to Hongsawadi,

212
00:20:03,657 --> 00:20:06,640
I shall petition Grandfather to issue a Royal Decree.

213
00:20:06,920 --> 00:20:08,621
Should anyone dare to call you a captive,

214
00:20:08,640 --> 00:20:11,400
- their tongue shall be severed as punishment.
- Listen to me.

215
00:20:16,480 --> 00:20:19,881
That way lies Hongsawadi, and this way is Ayutthaya.

216
00:20:21,240 --> 00:20:23,280
If you truly say I am no captive,

217
00:20:24,040 --> 00:20:27,520
then tomorrow, instead of Hongsawadi, may I take my siter back to Ayutthaya?

218
00:20:33,057 --> 00:20:34,520
Would your soldiers

219
00:20:37,880 --> 00:20:41,200
strike me down, just as they slaughtered those captives today?

220
00:20:50,800 --> 00:20:52,801
[The Grand Palace of Hongsawadi]

221
00:21:17,760 --> 00:21:20,000
It was never my wish for us to be a vassal of Hongsawadi.

222
00:21:21,040 --> 00:21:22,920
But King Bayinnaung possesses vast power.

223
00:21:23,481 --> 00:21:26,880
Our forces are few. We cannot contend with him.

224
00:21:28,177 --> 00:21:30,680
Though Nares has grown strong,

225
00:21:31,120 --> 00:21:32,121
Ayutthaya

226
00:21:32,680 --> 00:21:34,920
has lost too many of its commanders and generals.

227
00:21:38,957 --> 00:21:41,240
To wage war against Hongsawadi at this hour

228
00:21:41,903 --> 00:21:43,004
would end only in defeat.

229
00:21:48,423 --> 00:21:49,600
Perhaps...

230
00:21:50,560 --> 00:21:52,040
for the both of you

231
00:21:53,160 --> 00:21:55,400
to remain close to King Bayinnaung

232
00:21:56,017 --> 00:21:57,600
might prove to be for the best.

233
00:22:12,520 --> 00:22:14,040
Suphankalaya.

234
00:22:17,800 --> 00:22:19,801
You must entrust yourself to his care.

235
00:22:21,880 --> 00:22:24,040
Gain his absolute trust.

236
00:22:38,640 --> 00:22:42,560
Keep a keen ear for their internal movements.

237
00:22:45,523 --> 00:22:47,360
And find a way to send word back to us.

238
00:22:54,040 --> 00:22:55,500
It brings me great joy

239
00:22:55,757 --> 00:22:59,281
that you, Princess Suphankalaya, have graced Hongsawadi with your presence.

240
00:23:00,680 --> 00:23:02,800
Make yourself at home and find peace within these walls.

241
00:23:03,480 --> 00:23:05,560
Once the Royal Astrologers have found an auspicious day,

242
00:23:06,040 --> 00:23:07,720
I shall hasten the ceremony

243
00:23:08,410 --> 00:23:11,240
to appoint you as our Queen.

244
00:23:12,210 --> 00:23:14,360
So that Ayutthaya and Hongsawadi

245
00:23:15,040 --> 00:23:17,920
may remain as one Golden Land forevermore.

246
00:23:21,240 --> 00:23:22,880
You are most gracious, Your Majesty.

247
00:23:29,977 --> 00:23:32,840
I offer my undying loyalty

248
00:23:33,720 --> 00:23:34,880
at your feet.

249
00:23:36,120 --> 00:23:38,881
Having been parted from my home and kingdom, I stand here alone.

250
00:23:39,680 --> 00:23:41,000
From this day forth,

251
00:23:42,160 --> 00:23:46,040
I seek refuge beneath your royal protection

252
00:23:47,170 --> 00:23:49,360
until the very end of my days.

253
00:23:50,720 --> 00:23:52,240
Cast away your fears.

254
00:23:54,310 --> 00:23:55,360
From this moment forth,

255
00:23:56,200 --> 00:23:59,480
consider Hongsawadi as your home.

256
00:24:00,800 --> 00:24:03,400
Whatever brings you joy and comfort, simply ask.

257
00:24:04,840 --> 00:24:06,000
It shall be provided.

258
00:24:06,760 --> 00:24:08,400
You need not worry or grieve anymore.

259
00:24:09,680 --> 00:24:11,360
You are most gracious, Your Majesty.

260
00:24:22,720 --> 00:24:24,721
[Kuy Village]

261
00:24:45,160 --> 00:24:46,161
So, here you are.

262
00:24:49,120 --> 00:24:51,080
I sought you at your chambers, but you were gone.

263
00:24:52,683 --> 00:24:53,720
I came seeking my Muang.

264
00:24:54,810 --> 00:24:58,000
After months at war, he has grown quite a bit.

265
00:25:01,960 --> 00:25:04,280
Do you know?

266
00:25:05,040 --> 00:25:06,800
The Great King has commanded a palace to be built

267
00:25:06,903 --> 00:25:09,360
in the very style of Ayutthaya, just for your Sister.

268
00:25:10,760 --> 00:25:11,761
I know that.

269
00:25:23,470 --> 00:25:24,471
Hey.

270
00:25:25,490 --> 00:25:26,960
I have already petitioned Grandfather.

271
00:25:27,690 --> 00:25:31,040
He assured me he does not view your sister as a captive or a hostage in any way.

272
00:25:31,600 --> 00:25:33,000
My Father spoke out of turn.

273
00:25:35,360 --> 00:25:36,361
The King’s true intent

274
00:25:36,840 --> 00:25:39,520
is to forge a bond, to make our kingdoms true brothers.

275
00:25:40,280 --> 00:25:43,560
This new palace is built solely for her pleasure.

276
00:25:44,383 --> 00:25:46,120
Who would ever treat a captive with such grace?

277
00:26:46,090 --> 00:26:47,091
Mingyi Swa.

278
00:26:48,400 --> 00:26:49,601
Pay attention.

279
00:27:43,730 --> 00:27:44,731
Brother.

280
00:27:45,823 --> 00:27:46,824
You.

281
00:27:53,840 --> 00:27:55,041
How dare you!

282
00:27:58,960 --> 00:27:59,800
Father.

283
00:28:01,040 --> 00:28:03,240
It merely grazed me. I am unharmed.

284
00:28:04,400 --> 00:28:07,440
It was an accident. Prince Nares did not intend it.

285
00:28:19,243 --> 00:28:20,400
Listen to me, all of you!

286
00:28:23,240 --> 00:28:27,520
Mingyi Swa shall be the next Crown Prince of Hongsawadi!

287
00:28:30,440 --> 00:28:33,280
Whosoever causes my son to bleed,

288
00:28:33,530 --> 00:28:34,960
I shall inflict the severest of punishments!

289
00:28:35,543 --> 00:28:38,440
No leniency for anyone. Mark my words!

290
00:29:04,320 --> 00:29:06,321
[Mangjaparo, Royal Guardian]

291
00:29:32,437 --> 00:29:33,560
From this day forth,

292
00:29:34,817 --> 00:29:37,200
I shall have to keep a watchful eye on your blade, it seems.

293
00:29:38,720 --> 00:29:40,440
I have never harbored any intent to harm you.

294
00:29:44,090 --> 00:29:46,080
Are we still brothers?

295
00:29:49,160 --> 00:29:50,280
In the days to come,

296
00:29:52,323 --> 00:29:55,360
You shall be the Crown Prince of Hongsawadi.

297
00:29:58,910 --> 00:30:00,080
While I...

298
00:30:01,617 --> 00:30:03,482
am but a captive from Ayutthaya.

299
00:30:05,150 --> 00:30:06,920
How then, can we truly be brothers?

300
00:30:08,983 --> 00:30:09,984
Must you then…

301
00:30:11,423 --> 00:30:13,280
Be an enemy to your own brother?

302
00:30:15,160 --> 00:30:16,800
I seek only to be free.

303
00:30:23,200 --> 00:30:24,560
If in the days to come,

304
00:30:26,000 --> 00:30:29,080
Ayutthaya no longer bows to Hongsawadi,

305
00:30:30,360 --> 00:30:31,361
in that hour,

306
00:30:32,600 --> 00:30:35,480
would you still have the heart to call me brother?

307
00:30:42,960 --> 00:30:47,000
With such words, rebellion must already be in his heart.

308
00:30:47,557 --> 00:30:50,640
Nurturing a future foe. Do not let him go, Your Majesty.

309
00:30:51,857 --> 00:30:52,970
Nonsense.

310
00:30:53,617 --> 00:30:56,440
A champion elephant, a war-winning steed.

311
00:30:57,280 --> 00:30:59,000
They all began with a rebellious spirit.

312
00:31:00,960 --> 00:31:02,960
If we fear those with greatness and courage,

313
00:31:03,823 --> 00:31:06,040
where then shall we find worthy men to serve in the days to come?

314
00:31:08,520 --> 00:31:10,320
When Mingyi Swa ascends to greatness,

315
00:31:11,240 --> 00:31:13,241
he too shall need a loyal commander by his side.

316
00:31:14,120 --> 00:31:17,021
Just as King Tabinshwehti once had me.

317
00:31:18,600 --> 00:31:20,920
How can Your Majesty compare Prince Nares to yourself?

318
00:31:21,760 --> 00:31:24,761
My mother was the elder sister of King Tabinshwehti.

319
00:31:25,600 --> 00:31:28,640
You and the late King were brothers-in-law.

320
00:31:29,360 --> 00:31:31,360
But Prince Nares is nothing to us.

321
00:31:33,800 --> 00:31:35,701
A warrior like Prince Nares

322
00:31:36,960 --> 00:31:38,961
is not to be found in ten thousand men.

323
00:31:40,280 --> 00:31:43,680
If we do not make use of his prowess, it would be a grievous waste of such talent.

324
00:31:45,037 --> 00:31:46,038
Well.

325
00:31:48,030 --> 00:31:49,880
I shall take this matter into my own hands.

326
00:33:03,290 --> 00:33:04,291
Nares.

327
00:33:05,450 --> 00:33:08,520
You sent for me. May I ask what the reason is?

328
00:33:18,320 --> 00:33:22,680
A few days ago, King Bayinnaung came to see me.

329
00:33:25,360 --> 00:33:26,760
Your reward.

330
00:33:31,800 --> 00:33:33,120
My deepest gratitude, Your Majesty.

331
00:33:36,257 --> 00:33:38,120
The dance of Ayutthaya

332
00:33:39,600 --> 00:33:41,480
is so distinct from that of Hongsawadi.

333
00:33:42,883 --> 00:33:43,920
A most striking and unfamiliar sight.

334
00:33:50,843 --> 00:33:53,080
Ayutthaya is Ayutthaya.

335
00:33:54,520 --> 00:33:57,400
It can never be like Hongsawadi.

336
00:34:00,320 --> 00:34:01,721
Yet, though we differ,

337
00:34:02,920 --> 00:34:04,120
we can coexist.

338
00:34:05,130 --> 00:34:07,040
If every man of Ayutthaya

339
00:34:07,897 --> 00:34:09,210
casting aside prejudice and pride

340
00:34:10,790 --> 00:34:12,560
strives only to prove his worth

341
00:34:13,520 --> 00:34:16,440
and merit, as you have done,

342
00:34:17,240 --> 00:34:18,600
I would gladly

343
00:34:19,560 --> 00:34:22,640
honor them as equals to my own people,

344
00:34:23,877 --> 00:34:25,480
without a hint of disdain.

345
00:34:33,150 --> 00:34:35,240
Tell this to Prince Nares.

346
00:34:43,240 --> 00:34:44,640
With such words,

347
00:34:45,130 --> 00:34:47,403
it is clear that Hongsawadi no longer trusts us.

348
00:34:48,560 --> 00:34:49,561
No wonder.

349
00:34:50,857 --> 00:34:51,858
What is it?

350
00:34:53,158 --> 00:34:56,720
Jaisingh has ordered that I am no longer to practice swordplay with Mingyi Swa.

351
00:34:58,510 --> 00:35:00,360
So, would you have me train with the lance instead?

352
00:35:02,480 --> 00:35:05,760
The spear technique of King Bayinnaung echoes across the ten directions.

353
00:35:06,600 --> 00:35:08,840
In all of Hongsawadi, none can stand as his equal.

354
00:35:10,960 --> 00:35:13,720
Your Grandfather teaches it to no one but his own kin.

355
00:35:14,880 --> 00:35:17,000
Why do you remain so idle and indifferent to such a gift?

356
00:35:20,920 --> 00:35:24,680
It is not that I am idle, But I have little skill in this art.

357
00:35:25,410 --> 00:35:28,680
Should I perform poorly, it would only bring shame upon Grandfather's name.

358
00:35:30,720 --> 00:35:33,721
Knowing that, you must dedicate yourself even more.

359
00:35:34,600 --> 00:35:37,722
The spear technique is a discipline for a Great Commander.

360
00:35:39,120 --> 00:35:41,360
It was not taught to you before because your time had not yet come.

361
00:35:42,121 --> 00:35:43,800
But that time is now.

362
00:35:45,080 --> 00:35:46,840
You must surpass Prince Nares.

363
00:35:47,181 --> 00:35:49,000
For should the day come when he dares to rebel,

364
00:35:49,423 --> 00:35:51,040
You must be the one who prevails.

365
00:35:52,200 --> 00:35:54,960
Hongsawadi must never fall to Ayutthaya.

366
00:36:01,480 --> 00:36:03,520
The spear technique of King Bayinnaung

367
00:36:03,840 --> 00:36:05,520
is it truly as formidable as they say?

368
00:36:07,317 --> 00:36:08,440
Father once told me

369
00:36:09,280 --> 00:36:11,281
that King Bayinnaung conquered the ten directions

370
00:36:11,560 --> 00:36:12,750
all because of this very spear technique.

371
00:36:14,043 --> 00:36:17,280
What a pity that I have never witnessed it with my own eyes.

372
00:36:21,560 --> 00:36:22,760
If that is so,

373
00:36:24,363 --> 00:36:26,562
then Mingyi Swa shall hold the advantage over you.

374
00:36:37,123 --> 00:36:38,880
Is there truly no one else?

375
00:36:40,017 --> 00:36:42,400
Whose skill can rival that of King Bayinnaung?

376
00:36:46,730 --> 00:36:48,520
I have heard it told in whispers

377
00:36:49,377 --> 00:36:53,440
that there is but a single man whose skill even King Bayinnaung himself

378
00:36:53,960 --> 00:36:55,000
acknowledges and respects.

379
00:36:57,960 --> 00:36:58,961
Who?

380
00:37:06,657 --> 00:37:07,943
Phra Maha Thera Khanchong

381
00:37:09,960 --> 00:37:11,361
originally a Mon warrior.

382
00:37:12,320 --> 00:37:15,040
In his youth, he was conscripted to war.

383
00:37:21,513 --> 00:37:22,880
It is said that

384
00:37:23,440 --> 00:37:25,160
his 'Two-Handed Blade'

385
00:37:25,600 --> 00:37:27,080
was invincible.

386
00:37:48,023 --> 00:37:49,880
When King Bayinnaung took the throne,

387
00:37:50,520 --> 00:37:52,521
the Master refused to serve the Burmese

388
00:37:52,960 --> 00:37:53,961
and fled into the monkhood.

389
00:37:54,520 --> 00:37:56,521
The King tracked him down,

390
00:37:57,240 --> 00:37:59,241
yet out of deep respect for his mastery,

391
00:38:00,040 --> 00:38:01,280
he spared his life.

392
00:38:02,641 --> 00:38:04,320
But a vow was made

393
00:38:05,123 --> 00:38:07,800
that he would never touch a blade again for as long as he lived.

394
00:38:11,000 --> 00:38:12,601
If he is forbidden from ever touching a blade,

395
00:38:14,263 --> 00:38:16,400
how, then, can he pass on the secrets of his art?

396
00:38:18,200 --> 00:38:19,360
What a profound loss

397
00:38:20,403 --> 00:38:22,840
the 'Two-Handed Blade', once peerless in all of Hongsawadi,

398
00:38:23,517 --> 00:38:25,040
has been passed to no one.

399
00:38:25,800 --> 00:38:27,880
not a soul has witnessed its grace ever since.

400
00:38:44,880 --> 00:38:47,240
Please, Your Holiness.

401
00:39:27,837 --> 00:39:30,440
I offer my deepest soul in reverence to you.

402
00:39:35,003 --> 00:39:36,560
You are not of Pagan,

403
00:39:38,020 --> 00:39:39,440
Nor are you of common birth.

404
00:39:40,777 --> 00:39:42,280
To humble yourself thus,

405
00:39:43,600 --> 00:39:45,320
what is it that you truly seek?

406
00:39:49,910 --> 00:39:51,120
I come here

407
00:39:52,360 --> 00:39:55,240
seeking only your divine mercy, Your Holiness.

408
00:39:57,880 --> 00:39:59,320
For I have heard whispers of a time,

409
00:40:00,360 --> 00:40:04,160
before you entered the sacred monkhood,

410
00:40:05,161 --> 00:40:07,200
when your Mon sword technique

411
00:40:07,650 --> 00:40:09,801
was heralded as peerless in all of Pagan.

412
00:40:12,000 --> 00:40:14,800
The man who once gripped a blade and took lives is long dead.

413
00:40:16,737 --> 00:40:20,040
I have been reborn beneath these saffron robes.

414
00:40:21,120 --> 00:40:23,320
The memories of that past life no longer dwell within me.

415
00:40:24,890 --> 00:40:28,000
If you come only for the sake of that sword,

416
00:40:29,237 --> 00:40:30,440
then return to where you came.

417
00:40:30,960 --> 00:40:32,760
My father belongs to Phitsanulok,

418
00:40:33,480 --> 00:40:35,200
and my mother to Ayutthaya.

419
00:40:36,557 --> 00:40:39,720
Both have lost their lands and their homes to the Burmese.

420
00:40:45,480 --> 00:40:48,040
My brother and I were dragged away as captives,

421
00:40:49,063 --> 00:40:52,080
forced to live in shadows as prisoners stripped of all dignity.

422
00:40:54,520 --> 00:40:55,521
War…

423
00:40:56,600 --> 00:40:59,403
It is but a cycle of victory and defeat.

424
00:41:03,640 --> 00:41:04,790
Must the defeated

425
00:41:06,163 --> 00:41:08,000
remain defeated for all eternity?

426
00:41:17,063 --> 00:41:19,600
Had I possessed the mastery that you do,

427
00:41:21,164 --> 00:41:23,560
I would never bow my head to the Burmese,

428
00:41:23,917 --> 00:41:25,560
nor would I seek refuge within these temple walls as you have.

429
00:41:25,897 --> 00:41:26,898
Such bold and daring words.

430
00:41:37,000 --> 00:41:40,101
But the affairs of the world no longer concern me.

431
00:41:40,720 --> 00:41:41,721
You should depart now.

432
00:41:42,790 --> 00:41:43,791
May you find peace.

433
00:42:47,677 --> 00:42:48,678
Who the hell are you?

434
00:42:48,957 --> 00:42:51,520
To strike at a monk with a blade, have you no fear of Hell?

435
00:42:52,757 --> 00:42:54,560
It is your blade I seek, Your Holiness.

436
00:42:55,320 --> 00:42:57,800
Even if I must suffer the fires of Hell, I shall not fear.

437
00:43:17,743 --> 00:43:18,744
My name is Nares.

438
00:43:19,720 --> 00:43:21,360
My sister is Suphankalaya.

439
00:43:22,143 --> 00:43:24,080
And my father is King Maha Thammaracha,

440
00:43:24,654 --> 00:43:26,087
Sovereign of Ayutthaya.

441
00:43:26,840 --> 00:43:29,160
My sister and I

442
00:43:29,670 --> 00:43:30,730
shall fight.

443
00:43:31,240 --> 00:43:33,080
We will never live as subjects under the yoke of Hongsawadi!

444
00:43:33,897 --> 00:43:35,680
I beg for your compassion.

445
00:43:42,930 --> 00:43:44,520
The plight of Ayutthaya

446
00:43:45,343 --> 00:43:47,120
What concern is it to a Mon such as I?

447
00:43:50,430 --> 00:43:54,520
The Mon people have fallen in battle, losing Hongsawadi to the Burmese.

448
00:43:55,630 --> 00:43:58,320
Your hearts must be filled with nothing but bitterness and rage.

449
00:44:00,357 --> 00:44:02,640
The hearts of Ayutthaya are no different.

450
00:44:05,703 --> 00:44:06,800
If our fates are one,

451
00:44:07,850 --> 00:44:09,760
why then, do we not stand together?

452
00:44:13,337 --> 00:44:15,120
On the day we reclaim our freedom,

453
00:44:16,200 --> 00:44:18,000
and break the chains of King Bayinnaung,

454
00:44:19,240 --> 00:44:21,950
the Mon shall be our brothers-in-arms.

455
00:44:22,910 --> 00:44:24,403
Whatever struggle you face,

456
00:44:24,977 --> 00:44:27,717
Ayutthaya's army

457
00:44:27,917 --> 00:44:29,437
shall march by your side.

458
00:46:32,557 --> 00:46:35,600
The Mon blade is sharp, resilient, and light as a feather.

459
00:46:35,803 --> 00:46:37,160
Its mastery lies in the 'Twin Blades'

460
00:46:38,080 --> 00:46:40,360
revolving like a relentless wheel.

461
00:46:41,560 --> 00:46:43,040
It creates an unbreakable shield.

462
00:46:44,217 --> 00:46:48,000
Neither sword, spear,

463
00:46:49,360 --> 00:46:50,400
nor arrow

464
00:46:51,890 --> 00:46:53,600
can pierce its dance.

465
00:47:08,110 --> 00:47:09,880
The partisan is the soul of a Great General.

466
00:47:10,720 --> 00:47:13,050
Though long and difficult to command,

467
00:47:13,640 --> 00:47:15,560
Once mastered,

468
00:47:15,797 --> 00:47:17,840
its reach is absolute.

469
00:47:18,520 --> 00:47:22,120
A single thrust can fell a hundred foes.

470
00:48:41,330 --> 00:48:42,600
How was it, Your Majesty?

471
00:48:43,880 --> 00:48:45,081
He still has much to learn.

472
00:48:50,217 --> 00:48:51,218
Ah…

473
00:48:52,280 --> 00:48:53,289
and what of Prince Nares?

474
00:48:54,607 --> 00:48:57,120
I have not seen his face for many suns now.

475
00:48:59,080 --> 00:49:01,840
Prince Nares has not been seen at the practice grounds for many days, Your Majesty.

476
00:49:02,963 --> 00:49:04,280
My scouts report

477
00:49:04,690 --> 00:49:06,920
that he leaves the palace every dawn

478
00:49:07,440 --> 00:49:10,520
and returns only at the fall of twilight.

479
00:49:11,557 --> 00:49:12,960
He speaks not of his destination/

480
00:49:14,890 --> 00:49:16,240
It is most peculiar, Your Majesty.

481
00:49:20,722 --> 00:49:22,240
Send someone to follow him.

482
00:49:23,783 --> 00:49:24,784
As you command, Your Majesty.

483
00:49:50,760 --> 00:49:52,761
Does Prince Nares not come here?

484
00:49:53,710 --> 00:49:54,711
No.

485
00:49:55,600 --> 00:49:56,640
Then where has he gone?

486
00:49:58,750 --> 00:50:01,840
Over there, he went into the forest with Muang.

487
00:50:03,903 --> 00:50:05,560
They will not return until the sun has long since set.

488
00:50:06,520 --> 00:50:07,521
Are you sure?

489
00:50:09,030 --> 00:50:10,440
Yes, young man.

490
00:50:11,240 --> 00:50:13,840
I speak no lies.

491
00:50:22,077 --> 00:50:23,640
And did the fool believe you?

492
00:50:24,263 --> 00:50:25,400
Yes, Your Highness.

493
00:50:27,200 --> 00:50:29,800
But my father sent me to warn you to be most cautious.

494
00:50:30,120 --> 00:50:31,880
Suspicion begins to take root.

495
00:50:32,680 --> 00:50:35,200
I shall be wary. And you too.

496
00:50:36,760 --> 00:50:39,440
I slipped away unseen, Your Highness. None have followed.

497
00:50:39,610 --> 00:50:40,611
Fear not for me.

498
00:50:43,640 --> 00:50:46,120
You must find a way out.

499
00:50:47,123 --> 00:50:48,124
That you have

500
00:50:48,810 --> 00:50:50,811
come to master the Mon blades under my tutelage,

501
00:50:51,880 --> 00:50:54,081
If this truth should ever reach the ears of King Bayinnaung,

502
00:50:54,837 --> 00:50:58,000
Our lives, both yours and mine, shall be forfeit.

503
00:51:23,517 --> 00:51:24,518
Good.

504
00:51:26,483 --> 00:51:28,360
You must learn to adapt, and do so swiftly.

505
00:51:32,243 --> 00:51:33,360
Phra Maha Thera Khanchong.

506
00:52:02,283 --> 00:52:03,284
Your Holiness.

507
00:52:09,403 --> 00:52:10,404
Who was it?

508
00:52:18,883 --> 00:52:21,040
The scent of your perfume, Brother Mingyi Swa

509
00:52:22,223 --> 00:52:24,480
is known to be more exquisite than any other in the land.

510
00:52:30,663 --> 00:52:32,200
Since you've graced us with your presence,

511
00:52:33,083 --> 00:52:34,840
Why not step out from the shadows and face me?

512
00:53:22,470 --> 00:53:25,280
The Mon blades the Monk taught you,

513
00:53:25,377 --> 00:53:27,200
you mean to use them against me, don't you?

514
00:53:27,208 --> 00:53:29,000
You are not my enemy.

515
00:53:29,003 --> 00:53:30,320
The Mohnyin rebels are invading.

516
00:53:30,400 --> 00:53:33,750
Uncle has sent a messenger to Hongsawadi, seeking our aid.

517
00:53:33,757 --> 00:53:36,600
And if Mingyi Swa becomes the Great Commander, what then?

518
00:53:36,783 --> 00:53:38,520
The Mohnyin are ruthless.

519
00:53:38,903 --> 00:53:41,960
A single poisoned bolt, and death is the only escape.

520
00:53:43,840 --> 00:53:46,360
My blade is for my enemies alone.

521
00:53:46,550 --> 00:53:49,560
Minye Kyawswa, you must ride out to war alongside your brother.

522
00:53:49,983 --> 00:53:52,160
Father, what would you have me do?
